From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OBS Packaging Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 14:20:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] opensbi: platform: generic: force single firmware region on
 SG2002

SG2002 only exposes eight PMP entries. When the CV18xx reset driver maps the
RTCSYS syscon into the root domain, the generic platform's default split
firmware layout consumes one PMP entry too many and boot aborts before
U-Boot starts.

Set the generic platform's single-firmware-region hook directly from
fw_platform_init() when the root device tree is compatible with
"sophgo,sg2002". This ensures the quirk is active before root domain PMP
regions are finalized, without depending on a separate platform override
module.

Signed-off-by: OBS Packaging Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>
---
 opensbi/platform/generic/platform.c | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/opensbi/platform/generic/platform.c b/opensbi/platform/generic/platform.c
index a24c17e..39534d5 100644
--- a/opensbi/platform/generic/platform.c
+++ b/opensbi/platform/generic/platform.c
@@ -68,6 +68,11 @@ static u32 generic_hart_index2id[SBI_HARTMASK_MAX_BITS] = { 0 };
 
 static DECLARE_BITMAP(generic_coldboot_harts, SBI_HARTMASK_MAX_BITS);
 
+static bool sophgo_sg2002_single_fw_region(void)
+{
+	return true;
+}
+
 /*
  * The fw_platform_coldboot_harts_init() function is called by fw_platform_init()
  * function to initialize the cold boot harts allowed by the generic platform
@@ -153,8 +158,17 @@ unsigned long fw_platform_init(unsigned long arg0, unsigned long arg1,
 	if (root_offset < 0)
 		goto fail;
 
+	/*
+	 * SG2002 only has eight PMP entries. Keep OpenSBI firmware in a
+	 * single PMP region so the RTCSYS syscon used by the CV18xx reset
+	 * driver still fits in the root domain PMP layout.
+	 */
+	if (!fdt_node_check_compatible(fdt, root_offset, "sophgo,sg2002"))
+		generic_platform_ops.single_fw_region =
+			sophgo_sg2002_single_fw_region;
+
 	fdt_driver_init_by_offset(fdt, root_offset, platform_override_modules);
 
 	model = fdt_getprop(fdt, root_offset, "model", &len);
 	if (model)
 		sbi_strncpy(platform.name, model, sizeof(platform.name) - 1);
-- 
2.50.0
